:name: ch32v003-smoke

# Minimal smoke test: load syzygy-dna.elf, step a few instructions, dump the
# PC. This validates that Renode accepts the platform description and the
# CPU can execute from flash. No peripheral models yet — accesses to
# unmapped MMIO will log warnings, which is what we want to see.

using sysbus
$elf?=@build-fw/src/syzygy-dna.elf

mach create "ch32v003"
machine LoadPlatformDescription @tests/renode/platforms/ch32v003.repl

sysbus LoadELF $elf

# Bootstrap: enable machine-external interrupt in mie. Real silicon's
# QingKe core gates only via PFIC enables, so ch32fun never writes mie;
# Renode's stock RV32 CPU needs mie.MEIE set for cpu@11 to dispatch.
cpu MIE 0x800

# ch32fun's vector table is at flash[0], with the reset entry pointed to by
# the first word. Renode's LoadELF sets PC from the ELF entry point
# (InterruptVector) automatically, so no explicit `cpu PC` is needed.

# 48 MHz core, ~1 IPC for simple sequences. The MIPS rating sets how much
# wall-clock-equivalent work Renode does per RunFor budget; bumping it up
# is the difference between "trapped in a 1 ms calibration delay" and
# "reached main()".
cpu PerformanceInMips 50
logLevel 0
logLevel 0 sysbus

echo ""
echo "=== Loaded ==="
sysbus FindSymbolAt `cpu PC`
echo ""

emulation RunFor "1.0"

echo ""
echo "=== After 1.0s emulated ==="
cpu PC
sysbus FindSymbolAt `cpu PC`

# Sanity check: firmware should have configured I2C1 by now.
# OADDR1 = address_7bit << 1 (so 0x35 -> 0x6A). CTLR1 should have PE | ACK.
echo ""
echo "I2C1.CTLR1 (expect 0x401 = PE | ACK)"
sysbus ReadDoubleWord 0x40005400
echo "I2C1.OADDR1 (expect 0x6A for I2C address 0x35)"
sysbus ReadDoubleWord 0x40005408

quit
